subSubSection.paragraph:
The second segment (tetrasternum) oval and with three setae on medial region. The third segment (penta- sternum) rounded, smaller than the second segment, has two setae on medial region. Metasternum longitudinally divided (
Fig. 11B
).

Chelicera.
Presents a mesal row of three teeth on the basal segment of the chelicerae with the first in the proximal region, with two cuspids, follow by one tooth shorter in the medial portion, and the third bigger than others placed in the distal region (
Fig. 11D
). The ectal row of the basal segment of the chelicerae have three teeth, two with acuminated apex placed in the proximal portions, fused at the base (tooth 1 and 2), and one more with acuminate apex placed on the medial portion (tooth 3) (
Fig. 11F
). Mobile finger of the chelicerae with five teeth.
